<subSubSection id="48C48DB690A05A4D84507C9A728BAB88" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="96532DE265FAC2247ED7B9B3A387F7F9" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48097CCF3A0C6605AD11D7D82D49D614" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">Small species (2-3.5 mm length), cylindrical with widest near shoulders; antenna serrate beyond antennomere V, antennomeres III-IV slightly widened, but not dilated distally; pronotum with various bumps and short ridges, posterior pronotal lobe concave, usually without well differentiated notch.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1A2AC1946E4E4661EE010FA2C4C776A1" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="14B4A332B4AFA4470CFEF9B2A80DD1FD" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2867FB8728B7B4965F814538C247A5FC" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">
Present in Nearctic, Neotropical, and Oriental regions (
<bibRefCitation id="639591AC38B4CCD9AF375E5E1C48FDFC" author="Monros, F" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Lilloana" pageId="61" pageNumber="72" pagination="489 - 672" title="Revision de las especies argentinas de Chlamisinae (Col., Chrysomelidae) (5 ª contribucion al conocimiento de Chlamisinae)." volume="10" year="1951 c">
<normalizedToken id="AD7A6C062BA2C66725847885850910ED" originalValue="Monrós">Monros</normalizedToken>
1951c
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="37B65CAC67DDBAC60954C597C298160F" author="Karren, JB" journalOrPublisher="The University of Kansas Science Bulletin" pageId="59" pageNumber="70" pagination="647 - 695" title="A revision of the genus Exema of America, north of Mexico (Chrysomelidae, Coleoptera)." volume="46" year="1966">Karren 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Includes 26 species, 10 represented in the Neotropics.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88BC2FA9328B375D4C2B18D28A05AA52" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7F2FF0629D66A6B28C0B0F905BBC0365" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="560CB918389D9553A863EAE3F1DC5105" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">
<bibRefCitation id="9D6586DDA025A45AAA221A482D9A23D0" author="Gressitt, JL" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Insects Monograph" pageId="58" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 299" title="The Chrysomelidae (Coleopt.) of China and Korea Part I" volume="1 A" year="1961">Gressitt and Kimoto (1961)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized this genus with 
<taxonomicName id="AACB5546C1F7D51CC45F166C6FE01724" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chlamisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chlamisus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chlamisus</taxonomicName>
, yet, this decision has been ignored and is considered to be a valid genus (
<bibRefCitation id="3438C6C71E06ADFC5D5E6768B7931709" author="Karren, JB" journalOrPublisher="The University of Kansas Science Bulletin" pageId="59" pageNumber="70" pagination="647 - 695" title="A revision of the genus Exema of America, north of Mexico (Chrysomelidae, Coleoptera)." volume="46" year="1966">Karren 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DF27A2468EB9B22BAEC952E132433F22" author="Karren, JB" journalOrPublisher="The University of Kansas Science Bulletin" pageId="59" pageNumber="70" pagination="875 - 988" title="A revision of the subfamily Chlamisinae of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)." volume="49" year="1972">1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DF1AB4542D3F55193F35F71C70DBF39A" author="Seeno, TN" journalOrPublisher="Entomography" pageId="63" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 221" title="Leaf Beetle Genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)." volume="1" year="1982">Seeno and Wilcox 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="52E48B1E27E9622323BAF0531252B4E8" author="Riley, EG" journalOrPublisher="Coleopterists Society Special Publication 1, Sacramento" pageId="62" pageNumber="73" title="Catalog of the leaf beetles of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Megalopodidae, Orsodacnidae and Chrysomelidae, excluding Bruchinae)." year="2003">Riley et al., 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The relationship among 
<taxonomicName id="7A4F0AAE5ADADB82E7212835F5EF348F" lsidName="" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" rank="tribe" tribe="Fulcidacini">Fulcidacini</taxonomicName>
genera remains to be studied.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0A67F780577EB52DF7965BE9F24BEBAD" pageId="44" pageNumber="55" type="argentinian species checklist">
<paragraph id="B030A6EE1CEF520D63AD14D840F4F30D" pageId="44" pageNumber="55">Argentinian species checklist.</paragraph>
